
 Licence Agreement
 -----------------

  The following short licence  agreement  is  written  in  english,  but
  because  "HousePool"  is  a  german  product,  we  see  no need for an
  complete english licence agreement.
  But some important legal things in english:


 Things you are NOT ALLOWED to do:

 - you are NOT allowed to mirror the html-pages on you web-server
   or site without a written permission of the HousePool Magazine.

 - you are NOT allowed to publish it on a DISK with a price over
   5 DM/5 SFR/2 £/5 $ or on a CDROM with a price over 25 DM/25 SFR/
   10 £/25 $ without written permission.

 - you are NOT allowed to earn any money with the product HousePool
   except the following point:
   - you may sell HousePool on a DISK or a CDROM, if the price is
     under the above given limits. BUT please if you put it on some
     DISK and/or CDROM, send us a copy.

 - you are NOT allowed to perform HousePool on a commercial public
   presentation without the given written permission of HousePool.


 What you CAN do without any further permission:

 - copy the Amigaguide Version as much as you can - but don´t sell
   it for prices above the given limits !

 - tell everybody what a fine magazine HousePool is

 - show it your friends on a private presantation

 - put it on a CDROM, which you might produce - but watch the given
   price limits !

 - read or use it as much as you want to !

 - make a remix of the HousePool Anthem !


 IMPORTANT NOTE !

  All person (natural or legal entity), who will  act  contrary  to  the
  above condition and to the conditions mentioned in the german language
  legal- text-file, can expect civil juridical proceeding !


